	elseif key=="GnomeStandardAvoided" then text="Prima facie, you were not much affected by these events."
	elseif key=="GnomeStandardLostSomeone" then text="You have lost someone you loved during these events."
	elseif key=="GnomeStandardParticipated" then text="You had to fight back then. Luckily, you survived."
	elseif key=="GnomeStandardLostEverything" then text="You have suffered a lot during these horrible events. Your dreams will forever be haunted by memories of those you loved and lost, of twisted and broken devices, of crying children, of fresh graves..."

	elseif key=="GnomeZoneAvoided" then text=""
	elseif key=="GnomeZoneLost someone" then text="This is where someone you loved has perished."
	elseif key=="GnomeZoneParticipated" then text="You've been fighting here. Looks peaceful now, but is it for long?"
	elseif key=="GnomeZoneLost everything" then text="This is where you suffered a terrible loss..."
	
	elseif key=="GnomeZoneBadlands" then text="Despite its position between Stormwind and Dun Morogh, the Badlands have been Horde territory, so to say, \"traditionally\" - since Horde invaded Azeroth anyway. The Alliance is only represented by small camps of Explorer League's dwarves who are studying Uldaman - or trying to, not helped by the fact that the complex is overrun by Dark Irons and troggs.|n|nIn addition, Lotwil Veriatus, a revered magic researcher, conducts experiments in the northwestern part of the area."
	elseif key=="GnomeZoneTooltipBadlands" then text="Uldaman is a mistery that many try to uncover - both|nin the libraries of Ironforge and here in Badlands, in the field."
	elseif key=="GnomeZoneUn'Goro Crater" then text="Un'Goro is filled with exotic plant life and even more exotic creatures, and therefore is very attractive for natural scientists. An expedition troupe led by Marshal siblings has recently set foot into the crater.|n|nThe expedition has faced lots of unexpected issues, but its members still try their best to conduct the research. You might want to speak to J.D. Collie, who studies the crystals scattered all over the crater, and Karna Remtravel, the inventor of a mechanical ape."
	elseif key=="GnomeZoneTanaris" then text="Gadgetzan is the capital city of the Steamwheedle Cartel, the largest of the goblin cartels. Although goblins are known for their greed and narrow-mindedness, their city is the largest hub for engineering and research in the continent.|n|nNotable citizens are: Jhordy Lapforge, inventor of The Matter Transporter; Curgle Cranklehop, inventor of the Super Snapper and 	hippogryph protection activist; Pestlezugg, decently educated alchemist (a genius, by goblin standards)."
	elseif key=="GnomeZoneTooltipTanaris" then text="Yeh'kinya in Steamwheedle Port is known to be|nobsessed with some \"ancient prophecies\"."
	elseif key=="GnomeZoneStonetalon Mountains" then text="Stonetalon is important for night elves, sacred even. But right now, the land is in awful state. Venture Co ravages the eastern part of it, Horde occupies most of the center, and southwest is infested by harpies.|n|nEnlightened Assembly of Arcanology, Alchemy and Engineering Sciences sent Gaxim Rustfizzle here to show the night elves that they can greatly benefit from gnomish technology, as well as from magic. Maybe you could stop by and lend him a hand."
	elseif key=="GnomeZoneAshenvale" then text="Forests of Ashenvale is where the Alliance has first met the night elves. The contact was not a peaceful one... But later, understanding that demons of Burning Legion are a greater evil, night elves have joined forces with Alliance and Horde to repel the demonic invasion."
	elseif key=="GnomeZoneRedridge Mountains" then text="This seemingly-idyllic part of human Stormwind Kingdom was one of the important battlefields of First War. Eventually conquered by the orcish Horde, it has only returned to the Alliance a few years later.|n|nEven now, \"Dark Horde\", remnants of the old Horde, controls the Burning Steppes to the north and plagues Redridge with constant attacks."
	elseif key=="GnomeZoneBurning Steppes" then text="Blackrock Spire served as an orc stronghold during First and Second War. Orcs that live here today do not honor Horde's truce with the Alliance even formally.|n|nHere, during the Siege of Blackrock Spire, Anduin Lothar, the hero of humans and of the Alliance, was slain by cowardly orcs. Lothar's death turned the tide in the unexpected direction, and spurred the Alliance on to crush the failing Horde."
	elseif key=="GnomeZoneEngineerYes" then text="An aspiring engineer like you simply mustn't miss the opportunity to learn from a scientist of such level!"
	elseif key=="GnomeZoneEngineerNo" then text="Even though you are not keen on engineering, it is still very much worth your time to talk to a scientist of such level."

	elseif key=="GnomeAgeYoung" then text="\"Four years have passed since the mortal races banded together and stood united against the might of the Burning Legion\".|n|nYour childhood was quite peaceful, but during your teenage years the world was shackled by the demonic invasion known as Third War. Your small world was shackled even worse, when troggs invaded our good city of Gnomeregan and eventually overran it.|n|nPerhaps the stories of veteran troggslayers have made you hungry for heroic deeds, or maybe the horrors of the war have influenced your decision to become an independent adventurer.|n|nIn any case, you are an adult now, and your future is in your hands..."
	elseif key=="GnomeAgeThirdWar" then text="\"Four years have passed since the mortal races banded together and stood united against the might of the Burning Legion\". You were an adult when these events, known as Third War, took place.|n|nMost of us, however, fought their own war at that time. Troggs invaded our good city of Gnomeregan. Despite us fighting creatively and bravely for years, the city was lost...|n|nSome might have said before that the orcs are the greatest enemy the Alliance have ever faced, but we now know that there are greater horrors."
	elseif key=="GnomeAgePeace" then text="You were lucky enough to have a relatively peaceful youth. The orc invaders were defeated in the Second War, and only a few years ago the world have faced the wrath of their former masters - demons of the Burning Legion.|n|nMost of us, however, fought their own war at that time. Troggs invaded our good city of Gnomeregan. Despite us fighting creatively and bravely for years, the city was lost...|n|nYou know that the eternal peace is impossible, but you have at least felt the taste it."
	elseif key=="GnomeAgeSecondWar" then text="You were an adult when gnomes and dwarves have joined the Alliance to oppose the bloodthirsty Horde.|n|nThe Second War was the great victory of your youth. A decade of relative peace followed, and only a few years ago the world have faced the wrath of demons of the Burning Legion, former masters of orcs.|n|nMost of us, however, fought their own war at that time. Troggs invaded our good city of Gnomeregan. Despite us fighting creatively and bravely for years, the city was lost...|n|nYou know that even if an enemy is defeated, another foe always lurks in shadows, only waiting for the proper moment to attack."
	elseif key=="GnomeAgeWarofThreeHammers" then text="You are not some youngling I see! You remember a different world - world without orcs, world consisting of only one continent. You even remember when dwarven clans fought each other in a bloody civil war.|n|nCenturies passed like one day, didn't they? Wars followed each other, and the last of them had devastating consequences on our society. Of course, I mean trogg invasion of our good city of Gnomeregan. Despite us fighting creatively and bravely for years, the city was lost..."
	elseif key=="GnomeAgeKingMechagon" then text="You are not some youngling I see! You remember a different world - world without orcs, world consisting of only one continent. You even remember when our society was ruled by a king but not by an elected High Tinker!|n|nCenturies passed like one day, didn't they? Wars followed each other, and the last of them had devastating consequences on our society. Of course, I mean trogg invasion of our good city of Gnomeregan. Despite us fighting creatively and bravely for years, the city was lost..."
	
	elseif key=="GnomeEngineer" then text="Before we start, I would like to raise a somewhat delicate issue. Are you an engineer?"
	elseif key=="GnomeEngineerYes" then text="Of course you are! Many of us are renowned engineers, mechanics, and technicians, widely respected for their knowledge of the scientific facets of the world and their ability to transform said knowledge into surprising tools, vehicles, armor, and weapons.|n|nMuch of our philosophy is focused on forward-thinking, inventive concepts; little thought is usually given to history or non-scientific records. But in my personal opinion, historical events are often exciting to discuss! So shall we proceed?"
	elseif key=="GnomeEngineerNo" then text="Of course you are not! Many of us are renowned engineers, mechanics, and technicians - must be annoying to hear strangers ask about \"your latest invention\" solely for this reason? Our society consists of poets, pure mathematicians, doctors, teachers, tailors, sailors... One does not have to tinker just because he or she is a gnome!|n|nI must admit that engineering is important in our lives. Moreover, much of our philosophy is focused on forward-thinking, inventive concepts; little thought is usually given to history or non-scientific records. But in my personal opinion, historical events are often exciting to discuss! So shall we proceed?"	
	
	elseif key=="GnomeEventKingMechagon" then text="King Mechagon was the last gnomish king; we elect our rulers based on the merits of their work and their benefits to the race ever since. About four hundred years ago, the king lead his followers in search of a mystical land of technology."	
	elseif key=="GnomeEventKingMechagonStandard" then text="This is pretty much the whole story. Nothing is known about the fate of the king and his expedition. There might have been some (or many) casualties during this risky (some would say crazy) affair."	
	elseif key=="GnomeEventWarofThreeHammers" then text="Death of the dwarven king Modimus Anvilmar marked the beginning of War of the Three Hammers. Bronzebeards, Wildhammers, and Dark Irons have been fighting to control the Ironforge.|n|nThese were dark times for us. Dwarven nobles fight each other, crazed with their lust for power, while innocent inhabitants of the area, gnomes and dwarves alike, become refugees or even lose their lives."	
	elseif key=="GnomeEventWarofThreeHammersStandard" then text="In the end, Bronzebeards and Wildhammers made peace that stays strong to this day. Dark Irons, on the other hand, fight the other two clans to this day.|n|nMost of us were lucky enough to avoid the war of dwarves."	
	elseif key=="GnomeEventFirstWar" then text="Orcs came from another world. These bloodthirsty savages have ravaged the human city of Stormwind couple decades ago."	
	elseif key=="GnomeEventFirstWarStandard" then text="The Alliance was not officially formed during the First War. When rumors have reached Gnomeregan, most have thought that orcs are a minor threat, like gnolls or murlocs..."	
	elseif key=="GnomeEventSecondWar" then text="Second War immediately followed the First one. The orcs have bolstered ranks of the Horde with forest trolls, orges, and goblins, and continued to advance north. After devastation of Stormwind City, the whole continent was in danger of facing the same fate."	
	elseif key=="GnomeEventSecondWarStandard" then text="The denizers of Azeroth - gnomes, dwarves, humans of the Seven Kingdoms, and high elves - have stood together against the Horde. Gnomeregan was besieged, and the rest of Khaz Modan fell to the orcs, including even Wetlands...|n|nBut after a long and bloody war, we emerged victorious."	
	elseif key=="GnomeEventGnomeregan" then text="Dwarven digging operations around Uldaman awoke the foul race of primitive creatures called troggs, which were attracted to our machinery and built tunnels toward Gnomeregan. They broke through the lower reaches of the city, invading from the depths of the earth.|n|nHigh Tinker Gelbin Mekkatorque, knowing that the Alliance was already busy with the demonic invasion known as Third War, made a noble attempt to handle this subterranean invasion without Alliance aid. For five years, we fought the troggs in secret..."	
	elseif key=="GnomeEventGnomereganStandard" then text="But we were overrun. Then, High Tinker's top adviser and friend Mekgineer Sicco Thermaplugg put forward a potential plan: to release a toxic gas that would kill the troggs as they invaded.|n|nYou can speak with High Tinker himself when the time comes. Long story short, the plan failed. The gas was much deadlier than anyone anticipated.|n|nEight... Excuse me, it is difficult to stay unbiased and rigorous while talking about this tragedy. But eighty is just a number, isn't it? When put in such an abstract way, the fact that eighty percent of the Gnomeregan citizens were wiped out by the gas is less horrifying."	
	elseif key=="GnomeEventThirdWar" then text="While most of us tried to banish troggs from Gnomeregan, the plague happened far to the north. Kingdom of Lordaeron, former capital of the Alliance, found itself infested by the undead.|n|nArthas, prince of Lordaeron, travelled to Northrend with the mission to stop it. There, some dark force changed him... Young paladin became a death knight, and led the undead to ravage his own Kingdom."	
	elseif key=="GnomeEventThirdWarStandard" then text="Survivors of Lordaeron, as well as the other members of the Alliance, sailed across the Sea to Kalimdor. There, the final battle of the Third War happened. The undead turned out to be mere servants of the demons of Burning Legion. The Horde turned out to be able to listen to a reason, and to assist the Alliance heroes in saving the world.|n|nUltimately, the united forces of dwarves, humans, elves, orcs, trolls, tauren - all greatly strengthened by gnomish technology! - were able to defeat the demons during the Battle for Mount Hijal.|n|nOnly then, the Alliance learnt about the devastation of Gnomeregan that most of us desperately tried to prevent. Only then they learnt of the sacrifice we made in order to not split the Alliance army."	
