	elseif key=="OrcZoneAvoided" then text=""
	elseif key=="OrcZoneLost someone" then text="Maybe this is where someone you loved has perished."
	elseif key=="OrcZoneParticipated" then text="You have been fighting here. Looks peaceful now, but is it for long?"
	elseif key=="OrcZoneLost everything" then text="This is where you suffered a terrible loss..."

	elseif key=="OrcZoneDustwallow Marsh" then text="Our allies, the ogres of Stonemaul, live nearby, in Brackenwall Village. Our enemies, humans, have a city of Theramore in the area, and fortified guard towers along the road.|n|nRight now, at least officially, there is a truce in this region. Warchief Thrall made it clear that he does not want humans of Jaina to be extinguished. But just few years ago, admiral Proudmoore, Jaina's father, and his Kul Tiras marines have launched a violent attack on the Horde."
	elseif key=="OrcZoneAlterac Mountains" then text="About thirty years ago, most of the orcs fell into the demonic trap and drank the cursed blood of Mannoroth. Frostwolves refused. Now it is clear that the clan's leader Durotan made the wisest decision, but back then, he and his orcs were exiled for the \"treachery\".|n|nThe Frostwolf clan made Alterac Valley its new home. They have mostly avoided the horrors of the war against Alliance. Few years ago, many Frostwolves joined the New Horde of Thrall.|n|nSome of them returned to Alterac, hoping to maintain neutrality. But Alliance greed shattered their hopes. Impudent dwarves invaded the Frostwolf territory, and the conflict grows stronger with each passing day."
	elseif key=="OrcZoneClanFrostwolf" then text="Perhaps one day you will fight for your clan's homeland."
	elseif key=="OrcZoneWetlands" then text="During the war against Alliance, the Dragonmaw clan took dwarven fortress of Grim Batol for a time. Later on though, dragons that we used as a weapon in that war got out of control and killed many orcs. The survivors fled south to the mountains, where they live to this day.|n|nDragonmaw clan is a part of \"Dark Horde\" these days. They are enemies to Thrall and to us all."
	elseif key=="OrcZoneClanDragonmaw" then text="However, you should not be ashamed of your past. Other Dragonmaws might have made the wrong decision, pledging their loyalty to maniac leaders of \"Dark Horde\". You made the right one."
	elseif key=="OrcZoneBlasted Lands" then text="This is where it all began. Dark Portal linked our Draenor homeworld with this world, Azeroth. We entered it to conquer, but we could not.|n|nThrall formed the New Horde, and Azeroth is now our home. Dark Portal is destroyed from Draenor's side, and Draeron itself is torn apart. Some believe that one day, Dark Portal will open again, and we can re-enter the ravaged world we lived in for centuries."
	elseif key=="OrcZoneTooltipBlasted Lands" then text="There is a spirit of a great Hero of the Horde|non the border with Swamp of Sorrows."
	elseif key=="OrcZoneBurning Steppes" then text="Blackrock Spire was once the Horde stronghold. First it housed Shadow Council - the warlock group that has tricked our race into demonic slavery. With the rise of Warchief Doomhammer, Shadow Council was disbanded, and Blackrock clan settled in.|n|nSiege of Blackrock Spire took place when the war was ending, and it was lost. Doomhammer was captured by Alliance pigs...|n|nThese days, Blackrock clan still inhabits the Spire, but it is no longer a part of the Horde. In fact, they are the main clan of the corrupt \"Dark Horde\"."
	elseif key=="OrcZoneClanBlackrock" then text="Don't be ashamed by your past! You made it right, pledging your loyalty to mighty Thrall and not to maniac leaders of \"Dark Horde\"."
	elseif key=="OrcZoneClanTwilight's Hammer" then text="Many fanatics of Twilight's Hammer lurk in the area. Want to rejoin your clan here? Take part in their dark rituals - as an offering..."
	elseif key=="OrcZoneAshenvale" then text="Our logging operations in Ashenvale started during Third War. Soon, the truce with Alliance was made in order to fight the demons of Burning Legion, and we had to temporarily respect elves' \"rights\" to the forest.|n|nNow, the demons are defeated, and the conflict grows again. Despite disagreements from Thrall and the shamans, Warsong Outriders made their duty to ensure that the flow of timber from Ashenvale to Durotar continues. The elves keep fighting against it..."
	elseif key=="OrcZoneClanWarsong" then text="Perhaps one day you will join this battle - for the glory of your clan, and for the glory of the Horde!"
------------------------------------------------------------
	elseif key=="OrcAgeYoung" then text="\"Four years have passed since the mortal races banded together and stood united against the might of the Burning Legion\".|n|nYou were just a child when our mighty Warchief Thrall freed the orcs from human prison camps and led the New Horde to Kalimdor, to fight the demonic invasion.|n|nKalimdor is our home now. Demons are crushed, but there is no peace in our newfound home. Drums of war against Alliance thunder once again, and Horde shall prevail!"
	elseif key=="OrcAgeThirdWar" then text="\"Four years have passed since the mortal races banded together and stood united against the might of the Burning Legion\".|n|nYou were an adult when these events took place. Our mighty Warchief Thrall freed the orcs from human prison camps and led the New Horde to Kalimdor. There, we obtained our ultimate freedom, by defeating the demons who enslaved and corrupted us once.|n|nNow, Horde faces new challenges. Drums of war against Alliance thunder once again, and Horde shall prevail!"
	elseif key=="OrcAgeBetweenWar" then text="Your youth was a misery, "..Lorehelper_VarFrame.name..". War against Alliance was lost, and Draenor, our ancient homeland, was destroyed. Most of us have spent years in lethargy, in human prison camps...|n|nThen, our mighty Warchief Thrall freed the orcs and led the New Horde to Kalimdor. There, we obtained our ultimate freedom, by defeating the demons who enslaved and corrupted us once.|n|nNow, Horde faces new challenges. Drums of war against Alliance thunder once again, and Horde shall prevail!"
	elseif key=="OrcAgeWarsinAzeroth" then text="You were born on Draenor, "..Lorehelper_VarFrame.name..". When you were young, we left our ancient homeland to conquer Azeroth.|n|nHowever, it was not a war of our own. Warlocks fooled us, and demons corrupted most of us, made us their pawns.|n|nThis war was lost, and Draenor was destroyed. Most of us have spent years in lethargy, in human prison camps...|n|nThen, our mighty Warchief Thrall freed the orcs and led the New Horde to Kalimdor. There, we obtained our ultimate freedom, by defeating the foul demons.|n|nNow, Horde faces new challenges. Drums of war against Alliance thunder once again, and Horde shall prevail!"
	elseif key=="OrcAgeMiddleAge" then text="You are not a young orc, "..Lorehelper_VarFrame.name..". You have seen it all - demons corrupting most of us, war against draenei in our ancient homeland Draenor, war against humans in this new world of Azeroth. After losing the war, most of us have spent years in lethargy, in human prison camps...|n|nUnder the leadership of our mighty Warchief Thrall, we have freed our bodies from humans, and our minds from demonic blood curse.|n|nBut it is too early for you to retire. Drums of war against Alliance thunder once again, and Horde shall prevail!"

	elseif key=="OrcClan" then text="In the New Horde, most clan separations have disintegrated. We all fight for our Warchief as equal.|n|nAnd yet, your clan often matters. An honorable clan are the orcs whose example inspire you, these are orcs you want to be proud of you.|n|nWhat is your clan of birth?"
	elseif key=="OrcClanBlackrock" then text="At different times, Blackrock clan meant a great treachery and  a great glory. It was the ego of your leader, Blackhand the Destroyer, that allowed Gul'dan to corrupt our race. Later, however, our great Warchief Orgrim Doomhammer seized the power from that puppet of warlocks.|n|nThese days, leaders of \"Dark Horde\" call themselves Blackrocks. They remained steadfast to the \"ideals\" of the old Horde, including demon worship and depraved bloodlust. Rumors are, they are still slaves, not to demons but to another force that resides on top of Blackrock Spire.|n|nI am happy to see a Blackrock loyal to the New Horde. One day, \"Dark Horde\" will be no more, and Thrall will lead all orcs to the greater future."
	elseif key=="OrcClanBleedingHollow" then text="Bleeding Hollow clan is one of the most legendary ones. Your chieftain, Kilrogg Deadeye, lead the clan from earlier days of cowering from the arakkoa in the depths of the Tanaan Jungle, to eventual victory over the arakkoa and many more victories thereafter.|n|nThe clan fought with honor against humans in Azeroth. When Draenor, our home world, started to collapse, many of you managed to escape - only to be captured by humans.|n|nYears of imprisonment followed, but now, thanks to our great Warchief Thrall, we are liberated."
	elseif key=="OrcClanBurningBladeWarlock" then text="Not so much a clan as a vast asylum, the Burning Blade consisted of the best swordsmen of the Horde - and the most bloodlusty ones. So uncontrollable that they were only released to fight once during Second War - when Alliance laid siege to Blackrock Spire.|n|nI don't think you were one of them. Only a couple dozens survived the battle, and they all are famous Blademasters.|n|nI think you are a former member of the new-founded Burning Blade. The cult that opposes the New Horde and seeks to bring us back to the age of demonic slavery and bloodlust.|n|nI keep an eye on you, Warlock. You better slay the Burning Blade scum on sight to prove your loyalty to Warchief."
	elseif key=="OrcClanBurningBladeNonWarlock" then text="Not so much a clan as a vast asylum, the Burning Blade consisted of the best swordsmen of the Horde - and the most bloodlusty ones. So uncontrollable that they were only released to fight once during Second War - when Alliance laid siege to Blackrock Spire.|n|nI don't think you were one of them. Only a couple dozens survived the battle, and they all are famous Blademasters.|n|nI think you are a former member of the new-founded Burning Blade. The cult that opposes the New Horde and seeks to bring us back to the age of demonic slavery and bloodlust.|n|nYour past does not matter, as long as you prove your loyalty to Warchief - in particular, by slaying the Burning Blade scum!"
	elseif key=="OrcClanDragonmaw" then text="Thanks to Deathwing the Destroyer, the Dragonmaws found Demon Soul - an artifact of immense power that they used to capture the Dragonqueen Alexstrasza. This is why we had dragons fighting for the Horde in this war.|n|nLater, humans managed to destroy the artifact, and the freed dragons incinerated much of your clan. But some elements remain to this day in Wetlands. These forces are led by Nek'rosh Skullcrusher, who serves the self-styled warchief of \"Dark Horde\", Rend Blackhand.|n|nI am happy to see a Dragonmaw loyal to the New Horde. One day, \"Dark Horde\" will be no more, and Thrall will lead all orcs to the greater future."
	elseif key=="OrcClanFrostwolf" then text="I bow to you, Frostwolf. You were one of very few clans not to partake of the demonic blood which corrupted the other clans. For this, Gul'dan, pawn of the demons, declared the Frostwolves to be outlaws.|n|nFearing for the safety of his people, Durotan, father of our Warchief Thrall, led the clan to settle in the distant Alterac Mountains. Shortly thereafter, he and his wife Draka were murdered by assassins on the orders of Gul'dan...|n|nThroughout the Wars in Azeroth the Frostwolves remained in hiding, practicing the old traditions under the leadership of their shaman Drek'Thar. Eventually, Thrall sought them out. Under the tutelage of Drek'Thar, Thrall became a shaman and began a crusade to re-awaken the orcs to our heritage and free us from the demonic corruption that had plagued us for so long.|n|nThe Frostwolves who remain in Alterac now have been caught up in the new battle with the filthy dwarves. Maybe one day you will also fight for your clan's homeland."
	elseif key=="OrcClanShatteredHandRogue" then text="Your clan was named for an act of sacrifice made by Kargath Bladefist and his fellow orcs that lead to a successful rebellion and freedom from slavery under the ogres.|n|nMost of the Shattered Hand remained on Draenor, our home world, during the Wars in Azeroth. When Draenor started to collapse, many of you managed to escape - only to be captured by humans.|n|nWith the foundation of Durotar, the Shattered Hand has become the Horde's guild of assassins, training new rogues in the service of the Warchief.|n|nEven though you are a rogue of Shattered Hand, I imagine you'll need to earn the respect of your clan just as everyone else does - not by birth, but by your deeds."
	elseif key=="OrcClanShatteredHandNonRogue" then text="Your clan was named for an act of sacrifice made by Kargath Bladefist and his fellow orcs that lead to a successful rebellion and freedom from slavery under the ogres.|n|nMost of the Shattered Hand remained on Draenor, our home world, during the Wars in Azeroth. When Draenor started to collapse, many of you managed to escape - only to be captured by humans.|n|nWith the foundation of Durotar, the Shattered Hand has become the Horde's guild of assassins, training new rogues in the service of the Warchief."
	elseif key=="OrcClanTwilightsHammerWarlock" then text="So not only you are a shady Warlock, you are also from Twilight's Hammer. I wonder if I should smash your skull instead of chatting.|n|nTwilight's Hammer has grown to a cult greater than the orcs - and much, much darker. Obsessed with the idea that the Horde was the harbinger of apocalyptic doom to all the lands that it ravages, the clan felt a sacrosanct gratification in the destruction of all that it encountered. Its loyalty to the Horde was not as strong as its belief in its sacred mission of oblivion.|n|nWe would have probably executed all these lunatics if we could conquer the humans first! But we could not. The cult, now extended by all races of Azeroth, serves the Old Gods, seeking to destroy all creation.|n|nYour only way to redeem your past, Warlock, is to prove your loyalty to Warchief - in particular, by slaying the Twilight's Hammer scum!"
	elseif key=="OrcClanTwilightsHammerNonWarlock" then text="Twilight's Hammer has grown to a cult greater than the orcs - and much, much darker. Obsessed with the idea that the Horde was the harbinger of apocalyptic doom to all the lands that it ravages, the clan felt a sacrosanct gratification in the destruction of all that it encountered. Its loyalty to the Horde was not as strong as its belief in its sacred mission of oblivion.|n|nWe would have probably executed all these lunatics if we could conquer the humans first! But we could not. The cult, now expanded by all races of Azeroth, serves the Old Gods, seeking to destroy all creation.|n|nYour past does not matter, as long as you prove your loyalty to Warchief - in particular, by slaying the Twilight's Hammer scum!"
	elseif key=="OrcClanWarsong" then text="One of the strongest and most violent, your clan was also one of the most distinguished clans on Draenor. It then fought with honor against humans in Azeroth.|n|nWith the destruction of the Dark Portal the Warsong clan retreated to Stonard, and was forced into hiding in the wilds of Lordaeron. During this time, the chieftain of the clan, Grom Hellscream, was constantly battling the demonic curse that had left us all weakened and listless. Where other orcs gave in to this malaise, Grom fought it to the end of his days.|n|nLater reunited with Orgrim and Thrall, Grom was a hero of Third War as well. The cunning demon Mannoroth managed to corrupt him once more, but with Thrall's help, Grom was able to overcome the bloodlust, and the two faced and killed Mannoroth. This is how Grom freed himself at last - and freed us all.|n|nMany of Warsongs now fight in Ashenvale, where they are defending Horde's logging operations from the pesky elves. Maybe one day you will fight alongside your clan there."
	elseif key=="OrcClanMinor" then text="Don't be offended over the word \"minor\". It's just, many clans don't exist anymore.|n|nI'd be very surprised to hear that you identify yourself with Shadowmoon, or Bonechewer, or any other clan that perished with Draenor. Or with Stormreaver, most of whom were doomed by the power-lust of Gul'dan, their leader.|n|nBut even without great names in your past, you can make yourself a great future!"
	
	elseif key=="OrcEventWarwithdraenei" then text="Arakkoa and ogres were our main enemies on Draenor. With draenei, we lived in peace.|n|nIt all has changed when the draenei launched a seemingly-unprovoked massacre against the Bladewind clan. No Bladewind has survived to tell the details, but rumors began to spread that draenei are planning to destroy the orcs."
	elseif key=="OrcEventWarwithdraeneiStandard" then text="And so the orcs fought back - first sporadically, then, united under warchief Blackhand, in a more coordinated way. Gul'dan was another important figure in this war. In fact, Blackhand was his puppet, and Gul'dan himself was a underling of foul demons of Burning Legion...|n|nThe draenei were defeated, but the cost was great. Gul'dan and his warlocks shattered the last connection between us and the Elements of Draenor, and our world began to die. Most of the orcs were manipulated into drinking demonic blood that have been hazing our minds for decades to come."
	
	elseif key=="OrcEventWarsinAzeroth" then text="The Dark Portal was built in Draenor, and we used it to enter Azeroth. Mighty Orgrim Doomhammer has replaced the puppet warchief Blackhand, and human kingdom of Stormwind fell to our feet. We then ventured further north, to crush humans and their allies and conquer the continent."
	elseif key=="OrcEventWarsinAzerothStandard" then text="Gul'dan has betrayed the Horde in his lust for personal power. It splitted our forces, and Alliance got an upper hand.|n|nMany battles were won, but ultimately, Warchief Doomhammer was captured during siege of Blackrock Spire. Soon, humans destroyed the Dark Portal.|n|nMost orcs fled into wilderness, travelling in small packs or alone, under a constant threat of being imprisoned by humans. Some found themselves in Draenor, plotting retaliation..."
	elseif key=="OrcEventWarsinAzerothFrostwolf" then text="Gul'dan banished the Frostwolves from the Horde, and your clan had to flee north to find a new home. Hidden in Alterac Valley, most of the Frostwolves avoided the bloody war against Alliance and ultimate defeat of the orcs."
	
	elseif key=="OrcEventEndofDraenor" then text="The aging orc shaman Ner'zhul has seized control of the Horde on Draenor and reopened the Dark Portal. In search of new worlds to conquer, Ner'zhul tasked the  death knights - necromantic terrors created by Gul'dan - with acquiring artifacts of power located in different parts of Azeroth."
	elseif key=="OrcEventEndofDraenorStandard" then text="Ner'zhul used the power of the artifacts to call open innumerable dimensional portals. The influx of power tore Draenor apart... Most of the orcs who could flee to Azeroth were captured by Alliance soldiers."
	elseif key=="OrcEventEndofDraenorFrostwolf" then text="Most of the Frostwolves were lucky to remain in Alterac Valley during Ner'zhul's campaign. Only the most powerful shamans could feel how his reckless use of the artifacts tore Draenor apart..."
	
	elseif key=="OrcEventLiberation" then text="After years of pityful existence in human prison camps, we were liberated. Thrall began to free the orcs, to re-unite the clans under the banner of the New Horde."
	elseif key=="OrcEventLiberationStandard" then text="Camp by camp, Alliance was driven away, and more and more free orcs pledged loyalty to the Warchief Thrall. Sometimes, humans simply fled in fear; sometimes, a battle had to be won in order to break our shackles."
	
	elseif key=="OrcEventThirdWar" then text="Thrall had a vision - a vision that the demons of Burning Legion will soon return and unleash their wrath on Azeroth. He led the clans west, across the Sea, to Kalimdor.|n|nThe New Horde grew stronger as the Darkspear trolls and the tauren joined forces with us. And strength we needed, for the foe was great. The Burning Legion created the undead Scourge, and the armies of undead and demons marched to the north of Kalimdor, seeking to destroy the World Tree and the world itself."
	elseif key=="OrcEventThirdWarStandard" then text="Some members of the Alliance travelled to Kalimdor too, lead by the human mage Jaina Proudmoore. Our goals were the same - to repel the demonic invasion and to save our world. So a truce was made. Orcs, trolls, tauren, humans, elves, dwarves - only thanks to the bravery of us all, the Battle for Mount Hijal was won, and the demons no longer pose threat to our existence.|n|nDemons are no more, and the blood curse they have put on our race no longer binds us to their dark will. Mannoroth, the very being responsible for the corruption of the orcs, was killed by Thrall and his friend, Grommash Hellscream. Even though perished in this fight, Grommash will forever be remembered as Redeemer of the Orcs."

	elseif key=="OrcEventWarTheramore" then text="After the war with demons was over, Thrall have decided to stay in Kalimdor. The great Warchief Orgrim Doomhammer was Thrall's mentor and friend, and the capital city of Orgrimmar was given his name. The land itself was called Durotar after Thrall's late father.|n|nBut, before long, another war has began. Human admiral Daelin Proudmoore and his soldiers attacked the Horde, failing to understand that the New Horde has nothing to do with old demonic Horde."
	elseif key=="OrcEventWarwithTheramoreStandard" then text="Thrall did try to maintain peace, but humans only cared for vengeance. Daelin did not even listen to his own daughter Jaina, nor did he respect her truce with Thrall.|n|nUltimately, the humans were defeated, the fanatic admiral slain, and city of Theramore returned to Jaina's hands. Having a human city in such proximity may feel uncomfortable, but at least Jaina seems to be able to behave reasonably. Neither Thrall nor she wants a large-scale war."
